Male genitalia (
Fig. 23
): Moderately long, moderately sclerotized. Median lobe slender, moderately arcuate, slightly twisted basally, apex stick-like. Endophallus basally strongly folded, with some bristles towards apex. Parameres of about same length, dorsal one broader, slightly distorted, asetose.

Distribution: Known from Mindoro (
Philippines
) only.
